[start section id="20112"]

#1 Sigmoid colon cancer
I discussed with Mrs. Merchant as her endoscopy was performed with good prep by Dr. Emig all the way to the ileocecal valve, I do not think we need to repeat a full colonoscopy here.  We will have Dr. Tracy Singley perform a flexible sigmoidoscopy to verify the tattooing and to verify the location when he sees her on Friday.  I have asked her to prep with two enemas.  We will get a CEA as I do not see that this was checked locally or I do not have this report, and we will get a baseline chest x-ray.  I discussed with her if this reveals anything concerning, we will proceed to chest CT.  I discussed options for surgery including sigmoid resection versus low-anterior resection as it seems this is a distal sigmoid malignancy.  I do not suspect she will need a diversion with either of these procedures.  I discussed that her children will need screening colonoscopies at age 44 unless they develop symptoms earlier.
#2 Diverticulosis
She denies a history of diverticulitis.
#3 Indeterminate liver lesions
These are quite small, and I discussed with her we do not have a good modality to determine whether or not these appear to be metastatic disease or just simple cystic lesions.  I recommend that this be followed with scans in the future to make sure these are not changing with her malignancy.  Exact guidelines will be determined once she has her final pathology and lymph node status following surgery.
#4 Hypertension
Suboptimal control today, however, just recently started on blood pressure medicine.  We will get a CBC, BUN, creatinine, potassium, and sodium levels.  At this point will not change her medication, but this may need to be adjusted by her local provider.
#5 Obesity
#6 PAME
We will get a screening EKG and basic blood work and schedule POE nurse.
I will see Mrs. Merchant back on Friday with Dr. Singley following her testing.  All questions were answered.  She was seen with her husband.  Forty-five minutes spent.  Given laparoscopic colon handbook.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, not on file at HFCCS.
Code status discussion:  Discussed with Mrs. Merchant.  She would like to be a full code.

